.TH "TEXTENCODERSTREAM.WRITABLE" "3JS" "November 26, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TextEncoderStream.writable \- TextEncoderStream: writable property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]writable\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]TextEncoderStream\f[R] interface returns a
\f[CR]WritableStream\f[R] that accepts strings to be encoded into binary
data.
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]WritableStream\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
This example creates a \f[CR]TextEncoderStream\f[R] that encodes strings
as UTF\-8.
It writes some strings to the \f[CR]writable\f[R] stream, then reads the
encoded binary data from the \f[CR]readable\f[R] stream.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] stream = \f[B]new\f[R] TextEncoderStream();

\f[I]// Write data to be encoded\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] data = \(dq你好世界\(dq;
\f[B]const\f[R] writer = stream.writable.getWriter();
writer.write(data);
writer.close();

\f[I]// Read compressed data\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] reader = stream.readable.getReader();
\f[B]let\f[R] done = \f[B]false\f[R];
\f[B]let\f[R] output = [];
\f[B]while\f[R] (!done) {
  \f[B]const\f[R] result = \f[B]await\f[R] reader.read();
  \f[B]if\f[R] (result.value) {
    output.push(...result.value);
  }
  done = result.done;
}
console.log(\f[B]new\f[R] Uint8Array(output).toBase64()); \f[I]// 5L2g5aW95LiW55WM\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]TransformStream.writable\f[R]
